## ğŸ› ï¸ Technical Details

### Game Mechanics

- **Canvas Size:** 360px Ã— 576px
- **Character Size:** 46px Ã— 46px
- **Platform Size:** 60px Ã— 18px
- **Initial Jump Velocity:** -8
- **Gravity:** 0.4
- **Horizontal Movement Speed:** 4

### Features

- Smooth character movement with left/right animations
- Automatic jumping mechanics
- Dynamic platform generation
- Screen wrapping (character reappears on opposite side)
- Score tracking system
- Game over detection
- Restart functionality

## ğŸ“ Code Structure

- **index.html** - Main HTML structure with canvas element
- **style.css** - Basic styling for the game board
- **main.js** - Core game logic including:
  - Game initialization
  - Character movement and physics
  - Platform generation and collision detection
  - Score calculation
  - Game loop

## ğŸ¯ Game Logic

The game uses `requestAnimationFrame` for smooth animation and implements:
- Gravity-based physics for jumping
- Collision detection between the doodler and platforms
- Automatic platform scrolling when the doodler reaches 3/4 of the screen height
- Platform recycling system to maintain performance

## ğŸ› Known Issues

- Score calculation uses random values which may not reflect actual game progress accurately
- Consider implementing a distance-based scoring system for better gameplay

